Part 1. 100 Coding Exercises on HTML Forms and Input Elements
Each exercise is presented with:
Title & Learning Objective: A brief statement of what you’ll learn.
Code Example: A complete code snippet.
Explanation: A description of the code and key takeaways.
For brevity, the exercises are grouped into themed sections. (Exercises 1–20 cover basic form structure and simple inputs; Exercises 21–40 focus on additional input types and attributes; Exercises 41–60 cover advanced validation and grouping; Exercises 61–80 introduce form submission methods and styling; Exercises 81–100 integrate and extend the concepts.)
